# Troubleshooting Home Wi-Fi Connectivity and Website Loading Issues

## Overview
This project documents a real-world IT support troubleshooting scenario involving intermittent internet connectivity issues. Certain websites and images failed to load when connected to a home Wi-Fi network, while the same websites worked correctly on mobile data.

## Problem
The following issues were observed:

- Pinterest would not load.
- Images on websites failed to load.
- The issue occurred on both a laptop and a smartphone.
- Websites worked normally when connected to mobile data.
- The issue persisted across normal and Incognito browser sessions.

## Troubleshooting Process

### Step 1: Verify Device Connectivity
- Confirmed the laptop was connected to the Wi-Fi network.
- Verified that the smartphone was connected to the same network.

### Step 2: Test Browser Configuration
- Opened websites in Incognito Mode.
- Ruled out browser cache and extension-related issues.

### Step 3: Compare Across Devices
- Tested the same websites on both laptop and smartphone.
- Observed identical behavior on both devices.

### Step 4: Compare Different Networks
- Switched to mobile data.
- Confirmed that all affected websites loaded successfully.

### Step 5: Isolate the Root Cause
- Since multiple devices were affected only on the home Wi-Fi network, the issue was likely related to the router or network configuration.

### Step 6: Implement Fix
- Power-cycled the router by turning it off and on.
- Reconnected devices to the Wi-Fi network.

## Root Cause
The router likely experienced a temporary networking or DNS-related issue that prevented certain websites and images from loading correctly.

## Resolution
Restarting the router restored normal internet connectivity. All websites and images loaded successfully on both devices.

